{
  "stem": "26699.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The Jews were living generally in towns, and the Christians either in towns but mostly on the countryside.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So the Jewish community organized the schooling of their children.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I attended the first three years of my schooling in a makeshift school in a synagogue, where the synagogue hall was divided in four squares without any partitions in between, and there were four classes, like standard one, two, three, four, in the same hall.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was of course a little bit difficult when four teachers were teaching simultaneously, but this were the conditions where we learned the first years of schooling.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Were you aware of anti-Semitism?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, very much so.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Actually, Iasi was called the capital of anti-Semitism of Romania, where the Iron Guard had its strongest establishment.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the members of the Iron Guard, they were wearing green shirts to be distinguished from others, and they were very proud of this, and big fur hats like shepherds.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the way they were treating the Jews, I wasn't aware, because I was always protected by my parents.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But I still heard of beatings of Jewish students, before they were banned from the Iasi University, one of the oldest university-- if not the oldest university-- of Romania, with a long cultural tradition.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the Jewish students were beaten to pulp by this Iron Guard legionnaire called [?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Der ?] [?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Koligs. ?] This was the cultural center of Iasi.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I didn't of this sort.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I wasn't-- I was too small, and when I grew a little bit up, there were no Jewish students anymore at Iasi University.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were thrown out just before the Second World War.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My grandmother from my father's side was very religious.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "From my mother's side, they were, I would say, less.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
